cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

The paper deals with the privacy concerns related to personal data, specifically location data streams. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DB (Databases). The paper also proposes a framework for personalized privacy loss, which involves budget allocation and utility estimation, indicating that it could belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with trading mechanisms, which could suggest that it belongs to the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
